	<p>Your first example seems wrong, if you want the effect you are illustrating you should change the css to something like:</p>

 div {
      position: absolute;
      height: 100px;
      width: 100px;<br /><br />/* uncomment this to be sure it looks the same in all browsers:
      margin: 0px;
      padding: 0px;
      overflow: visible;
	<p>*/</p>
       }
 #one { 
     z-index: 3;
     top: 40px;
     left: 60px;
 }

 #two { 
     z-index: 1;
     top: 20px;
     left: 20px;
 }

 #three {
     z-index: 2;
     top: 60px;
     left: 0px;
 }

	<p>Off course you also have to add background colour and transparency(not widely supported yet).</p>
